    "for col in houses.columns:\n",
    "    if col != 'price':\n",
    "        sns.histplot(houses[col], kde=True, bins=30)\n",
    "        plt.title(f'Distribution de {col}')\n",
    "        plt.xlabel(col)\n",
    "        plt.ylabel('FrÃ©quence')\n",

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Initialiser les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "# Boucle sur chaque variable prÃ©dictive\n",
    "for predictor in predictors:\n",
    "    # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la rÃ©gression\n",
    "    X = sm.add_constant(houses[[predictor]])  # Ajouter une constante pour l'interception\n",
    "    Y = houses[target]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "    model = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extraire les mÃ©triques\n",
    "    r_squared = model.rsquared\n",
    "    I_r = np.sum(model.resid ** 2)\n",
    "    mean_y = np.mean(Y)\n",
    "    I_t = np.sum((Y - mean_y) ** 2)\n",
    "    I_m = I_t - I_r\n",
    "    p_value = model.pvalues[predictor]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Stocker les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "    results.append({\n",
    "        'predictor': predictor,\n",
    "        'r_squared': r_squared,\n",
    "        'I_r': I_r,\n",
    "        'I_t': I_t,\n",
    "        'I_m': I_m,\n",
    "        'p_value': p_value\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "# Trier les rÃ©sultats par les critÃ¨res (R^2 dÃ©croissant, I_r croissant, p-value croissant)\n",
    "results = sorted(results, key=lambda x: (-x['r_squared'], x['I_r'], x['p_value']))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "for res in results:\n",
    "    print(f\"Variable: {res['predictor']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  R^2: {res['r_squared']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  I_r: {res['I_r']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  I_t: {res['I_t']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  I_m: {res['I_m']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  p-value: {res['p_value']:.4e}\")\n",
    "    print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Meilleure variable\n",
    "best_variable = results[0]\n",
    "print(f\"La meilleure variable est {best_variable['predictor']} avec:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  R^2: {best_variable['r_squared']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  I_r: {best_variable['I_r']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  p-value: {best_variable['p_value']:.4e}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "528f9021",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation de la meilleure variable prÃ©dictive"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "49174501",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Train/Test Split\n",
    "Etape:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.Diviser les donnÃ©es :\n",
    "    -Divisez les donnÃ©es en deux ensembles : un ensemble d'entraÃ®nement (75%) et un  ensemble de test (25%).\n",
    "    -Utilisez train_test_split de sklearn.\n",
    "\n",
    "2.EntraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le :\n",
    "    -EntraÃ®nez un modÃ¨le de rÃ©gression linÃ©aire simple sur l'ensemble d'entraÃ®nement en utilisant la meilleure variable prÃ©dictive.\n",
    "\n",
    "3.PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de test :\n",
    "    -Utilisez le modÃ¨le pour prÃ©dire les valeurs de la variable cible sur l'ensemble de test.\n",
    "\n",
    "4.Calculer l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation :\n",
    "    -Calculez l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) entre les valeurs rÃ©elles et les prÃ©dictions sur l'ensemble de test."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 575,
   "id": "87623efc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : 7.2663\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diviser les donnÃ©es\n",
    "train, test = train_test_split(houses, test_size=0.25, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# EntraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le sur la meilleure variable\n",
    "X_train = sm.add_constant(train[['sqft_living']])  # Remplacez par la meilleure variable\n",
    "y_train = train['price']\n",
    "model = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de test\n",
    "X_test = sm.add_constant(test[['sqft_living']])\n",
    "y_test = test['price']\n",
    "predictions = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "mse_sqr = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions)\n",
    "#print(model.summary())\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {mse_sqr:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },

    "#RÃ©gression simple avec la meilleure variable prÃ©dictive\n",
    "#Dans votre notebook, vous avez identifiÃ© sqft_living comme la meilleure variable prÃ©dictive. Voici comment gÃ©nÃ©rer les prÃ©dictions pour le dataset houses_competition.csv :\n",
    "# submission_regression_simple_train_test_split.csv\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Charger le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition = pd.read_csv('houses_competition.csv', index_col=0)\n",
    "# Supprimer la colonne 'Unnamed: 0' si elle existe\n",
    "competition = competition.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "# print(competition.head())\n",
    "# PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour le modÃ¨le simple\n",
    "X_competition_simple = sm.add_constant(competition[['sqft_living']])  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire les prix avec le modÃ¨le simple\n",
    "predictions_simple = model.predict(X_competition_simple)\n",
    "\n",
    "# CrÃ©er le fichier CSV pour soumission\n",
    "submission_simple = pd.DataFrame({'ID': competition.index, 'Price': predictions_simple})\n",
    "submission_simple.to_csv('submission_regression_simple_train_test_split.csv', index=False)\n"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d6dae98c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Validation CroisÃ©e (K-Fold Cross-Validation)\n",
    "Etape:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.Diviser les donnÃ©es en K sous-ensembles :\n",
    "    -Divisez les donnÃ©es en K sous-ensembles (par exemple, 5 ou 10).\n",
    "\n",
    "2.EntraÃ®ner et Ã©valuer le modÃ¨le :\n",
    "    -Pour chaque itÃ©ration, utilisez K-1 sous-ensembles pour entraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le et le dernier sous-ensemble pour tester.\n",
    "    \n",
    "3.Calculer l'erreur moyenne :\n",
    "    -Calculez la moyenne des erreurs quadratiques moyennes (MSE) sur les K itÃ©rations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 577,
   "id": "6c839ca1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation moyenne (MSE) : 7.0169\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es\n",
    "X = houses[['sqft_living']]  # Remplacez par la meilleure variable\n",
    "y = houses['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# ModÃ¨le de rÃ©gression linÃ©aire\n",
    "model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Validation croisÃ©e (5 folds)\n",
    "mse_scores = -cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=5, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')\n",
    "mean_simple = mse_scores.mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation moyenne (MSE) : {mean_simple:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },

    "#RÃ©gression simple avec la meilleure variable prÃ©dictive\n",
    "#Dans votre notebook, vous avez identifiÃ© sqft_living comme la meilleure variable prÃ©dictive. Voici comment gÃ©nÃ©rer les prÃ©dictions pour le dataset houses_competition.csv :\n",
    "# submission_regression_simple_cross_validation.csv\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Charger le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition = pd.read_csv('houses_competition.csv', index_col=0)\n",

    "competition = competition.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "# EntraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le sur les donnÃ©es complÃ¨tes\n",
    "model.fit(X, y)\n",
    "# PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour le modÃ¨le simple\n",
    "X_competition_simple = competition[['sqft_living']]  # Utiliser la meilleure variable\n",

    "#1. Charger les donnÃ©es et prÃ©parer les variables\n",
    "#   Assurez-vous que toutes les variables prÃ©dictives et la cible sont correctement dÃ©finies.\n",
    "\n",
    "# DÃ©finir les variables prÃ©dictives et la cible\n",
    "X = houses.drop(columns=['price'])  # Toutes les colonnes sauf 'price'\n",
    "y = houses['price']  # La variable cible"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 394,
   "id": "ab671a86",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#2. Diviser les donnÃ©es en ensembles d'entraÃ®nement et de test\n",
    "#   Utilisez train_test_split pour diviser les donnÃ©es en deux ensembles.\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diviser les donnÃ©es en ensembles d'entraÃ®nement (75%) et de test (25%)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=42)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 395,
   "id": "e90c02f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<style>#sk-container-id-9 {\n",
       "  /* Definition of color scheme common for light and dark mode */\n",
       "  --sklearn-color-text: #000;\n",
       "  --sklearn-color-text-muted: #666;\n",
       "  --sklearn-color-line: gray;\n",
       "  /* Definition of color scheme for unfitted estimators */\n",
       "  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0: #fff5e6;\n",

    "# On peut aussi faire la validation croisÃ©e\n",
    "#6. Validation croisÃ©e (optionnel)\n",
    "#Pour une estimation plus robuste de l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation, utilisez la validation croisÃ©e.\n",

    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "\n",
    "# Validation croisÃ©e (5 folds)\n",
    "mse_scores = -cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=5, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')\n",
    "mean_mse_multiple = mse_scores.mean()\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation moyenne (MSE) avec validation croisÃ©e : {mean_mse_multiple:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f5a59ef2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "4.  SÃ©lection de variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "defb58e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Durant le TP nous avons vu le Forward Selection avec le RÂ² ajustÃ© comme critÃ¨re de performance et \n",
    "le critÃ¨re d'arrÃªt utiliser est le plus strict arrÃªt dÃ¨s que la performance diminue. Nous la mettos en oeuvre ici."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 404,
   "id": "10d64fe1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def forward_selection_adj_r2(data, predictors, target):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    ImplÃ©mente la mÃ©thode de Forward Selection en utilisant le RÂ² ajustÃ© comme critÃ¨re de performance.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - data : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es.\n",
    "    - predictors : Liste des noms des variables prÃ©dictives.\n",
    "    - target : Nom de la variable cible.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - selected_predictors : Liste des variables prÃ©dictives du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    - best_adj_r2 : Meilleur RÂ² ajustÃ© obtenu.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    selected_predictors = []  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "    remaining_predictors = predictors.copy()  # Variables restantes Ã  tester\n",
    "    best_adj_r2 = -np.inf  # Initialiser avec une valeur trÃ¨s basse\n",
    "    stop = False  # CritÃ¨re d'arrÃªt\n",
    "\n",
    "    while remaining_predictors and not stop:\n",
    "        iteration_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Testez l'ajout de chaque variable restante\n",
    "        for predictor in remaining_predictors:\n",
    "            # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es + la nouvelle variable\n",
    "            current_predictors = selected_predictors + [predictor]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la rÃ©gression\n",
    "            X = data[current_predictors]\n",
    "            X = sm.add_constant(X)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "            y = data[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "            model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Calculer le RÂ² ajustÃ©\n",
    "            adj_r2 = model.rsquared_adj\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Stocker les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "            iteration_results.append((predictor, adj_r2, model))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Trouver la variable qui amÃ©liore le plus le RÂ² ajustÃ©\n",
    "        iteration_results = sorted(iteration_results, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n",
    "        best_candidate, best_candidate_adj_r2, best_model = iteration_results[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # VÃ©rifier si le RÂ² ajustÃ© s'amÃ©liore\n",
    "        if best_candidate_adj_r2 > best_adj_r2:\n",
    "            best_adj_r2 = best_candidate_adj_r2\n",
    "            selected_predictors.append(best_candidate)\n",
    "            remaining_predictors.remove(best_candidate)\n",
    "            print(f\"Variable ajoutÃ©e : {best_candidate}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"RÂ² ajustÃ© : {best_candidate_adj_r2:.4f}\")\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            stop = True  # ArrÃªter si le RÂ² ajustÃ© diminue\n",
    "\n",
    "    return selected_predictors, best_adj_r2"
   ]
  },
  {

      "\n",

   "source": [
    "#DÃ©finir les variables prÃ©dictives et la cible\n",
    "target = 'price'\n",
    "predictors = [col for col in houses.columns if col != target]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Appliquer la mÃ©thode de Forward Selection\n",
    "selected_predictors, best_adj_r2 = forward_selection_adj_r2(houses, predictors, target)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "print(\"\\nMeilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ© :\")\n",
    "print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {selected_predictors}\")\n",
    "print(f\"RÂ² ajustÃ© : {best_adj_r2:.4f}\")"
   ]

   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "# Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation avec les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 1 : Diviser les donnÃ©es\n",
    "train, test = train_test_split(houses, test_size=0.25, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 2 : CrÃ©er un modÃ¨le avec les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_train = train[selected_predictors]  # Utiliser les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_train = sm.add_constant(X_train)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "y_train = train[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "model_selected = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 3 : PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de test\n",
    "X_test = test[selected_predictors]  # Utiliser les mÃªmes variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_test = sm.add_constant(X_test)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "y_test = test[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "predictions_selected = model_selected.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 4 : Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "mse_selected_r2 = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions_selected)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) pour les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {mse_selected_r2:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "037cc152",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Nous mettons en oeuvre ici, **le Forward selection** en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation(train/test split) comme critÃ¨re de performance pour la sÃ©lection des variables et comme critÃ¨re d'arrÃªt, ne vous arrÃªtez pas allez jusqu'au bout et gardez le meilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ©."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "373266ff",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "\n",
    "def forward_selection_mse(train, test, predictors, target):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    ImplÃ©mente la mÃ©thode de Forward Selection en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE)\n",
    "    comme critÃ¨re de performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - train : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es d'entraÃ®nement.\n",
    "    - test : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es de test.\n",
    "    - predictors : Liste des noms des variables prÃ©dictives.\n",
    "    - target : Nom de la variable cible.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - best_predictors : Liste des variables prÃ©dictives du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    - best_mse : Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    selected_predictors = []  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "    remaining_predictors = predictors.copy()  # Variables restantes Ã  tester\n",
    "    best_mse = float('inf')  # Initialisez avec une erreur trÃ¨s Ã©levÃ©e\n",
    "    best_predictors = []  # Meilleur ensemble de variables\n",
    "\n",
    "    while remaining_predictors:\n",
    "        iteration_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Testez l'ajout de chaque variable restante\n",
    "        for predictor in remaining_predictors:\n",
    "            # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es + la nouvelle variable\n",
    "            current_predictors = selected_predictors + [predictor]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la rÃ©gression\n",
    "            X_train = sm.add_constant(train[current_predictors])  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "            y_train = train[target]\n",
    "            X_test = sm.add_constant(test[current_predictors])  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "            y_test = test[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "            model = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de test\n",
    "            predictions = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "            mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Stocker les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "            iteration_results.append((predictor, mse, current_predictors))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Trouver la variable qui amÃ©liore le plus la performance\n",
    "        iteration_results = sorted(iteration_results, key=lambda x: x[1])  # Trier par MSE croissant\n",
    "        best_candidate, best_candidate_mse, best_candidate_predictors = iteration_results[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Mettre Ã  jour le meilleur modÃ¨le si nÃ©cessaire\n",
    "        if best_candidate_mse < best_mse:\n",
    "            best_mse = best_candidate_mse\n",
    "            best_predictors = best_candidate_predictors\n",
    "            selected_predictors.append(best_candidate)\n",
    "            remaining_predictors.remove(best_candidate)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Afficher les informations de l'itÃ©ration\n",
    "            print(f\"Variable ajoutÃ©e : {best_candidate}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {best_candidate_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {best_predictors}\")\n",
    "            print(\"-\" * 50)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            # ArrÃªter si aucune amÃ©lioration n'est obtenue\n",
    "            break\n",
    "\n",
    "    return best_predictors, best_mse"
   ]
  },

    "    \"All Variables\": mse_all,  # MSE pour toutes les variables\n",
    "    \"Forward Selection (MSE)\": best_mse,  # MSE pour le modÃ¨le Forward Selection\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les rÃ©sultats triÃ©s par MSE croissant\n",
    "sorted_results = sorted(results_comparison.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])\n",
    "print(\"\\nComparaison des erreurs de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) :\")\n",
    "for model, mse in sorted_results:\n",
    "    print(f\"{model}: {mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Identifier le meilleur modÃ¨le\n",
    "best_model, best_mse = sorted_results[0]\n",
    "print(f\"\\nLe meilleur modÃ¨le est '{best_model}' avec une erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) de {best_mse:.4f}.\")"

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 466,
   "id": "4e037b90",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par forward_selection_mse : ['sqft_living', 'lat', 'view', 'grade', 'yr_built', 'waterfront', 'bedrooms', 'bathrooms', 'zipcode', 'long', 'sqft_above', 'condition', 'yr_renovated', 'sqft_lot15', 'sqft_lot']\n",
      "Fichier de soumission crÃ©Ã© : submission_forward_selection_mse_tts.csv\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Charger le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition = pd.read_csv('houses_competition.csv', index_col=0)\n",
    "# Supprimer la colonne 'Unnamed: 0' si elle existe\n",
    "competition = competition.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par forward_selection_mse\n",
    "# Assurez-vous que `best_predictors` contient les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par forward_selection_mse\n",
    "# Exemple : best_predictors = ['sqft_living', 'bathrooms', 'bedrooms']\n",
    "print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par forward_selection_mse : {best_predictors}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# RÃ©entraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le avec toutes les donnÃ©es d'entraÃ®nement\n",
    "X_train_final = houses[best_predictors]  # Utiliser les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "y_train_final = houses['price']\n",
    "final_model = sm.OLS(y_train_final, sm.add_constant(X_train_final)).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour le modÃ¨le avec les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_competition_forward = competition[best_predictors]  # Utiliser uniquement les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_competition_forward = sm.add_constant(X_competition_forward)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire les prix avec le modÃ¨le obtenu via forward_selection_mse\n",
    "predictions_forward = final_model.predict(X_competition_forward)\n",
    "\n",
    "# CrÃ©er le fichier CSV pour soumission\n",
    "submission_forward = pd.DataFrame({'ID': competition.index, 'Price': predictions_forward})\n",
    "submission_forward.to_csv('submission_forward_selection_mse_tts.csv', index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fichier de soumission crÃ©Ã© : submission_forward_selection_mse_tts.csv\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1c5b9c9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Du coup ici nous avons choisir d'utiliser le Forward Selection en utilisant la probabilitÃ© critique comme critÃ¨re de performance \n",
    "pour la sÃ©lection des variables (pour ce critÃ¨re de performance, un seul critÃ¨re d'arrÃªt particulier peut Ãªtre utilisÃ© : arrÃªter lorsque toutes les variables \n",
    "sÃ©lectionnÃ©es sont significatives et qu'aucune des autres variables n'est significative une fois ajoutÃ©e). Significatif \n",
    "signifie une probabilitÃ© critique infÃ©rieure Ã  0..05."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 411,
   "id": "8cadc8ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "\n",
    "def step_selection_pval(train, v_s, v_nu, idx_t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Une Ã©tape de la sÃ©lection en avant basÃ©e sur la probabilitÃ© critique (p-valeur).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - train : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es d'entraÃ®nement.\n",
    "    - v_s : Liste des indices des variables dÃ©jÃ  sÃ©lectionnÃ©es.\n",
    "    - v_nu : Liste des indices des variables non encore utilisÃ©es.\n",
    "    - idx_t : Index de la variable cible dans le DataFrame.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - best_variable : La meilleure variable Ã  ajouter (ou None si aucune n'est significative).\n",
    "    - best_pval : La p-valeur associÃ©e Ã  la meilleure variable.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    best_pval = 1.0  # Initialiser avec une p-valeur Ã©levÃ©e\n",
    "    best_variable = None\n",
    "\n",
    "    for var in v_nu:\n",
    "        # Combiner les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es avec la variable actuelle\n",
    "        current_vars = np.append(v_s, var)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la rÃ©gression\n",
    "        X = train.iloc[:, current_vars]\n",
    "        y = train.iloc[:, idx_t]\n",
    "        X = sm.add_constant(X)  # Ajouter une constante pour l'interception\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "        model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # RÃ©cupÃ©rer la p-valeur de la variable actuelle\n",
    "        column_name = train.columns[var]  # Obtenir le nom de la colonne correspondant Ã  l'index\n",
    "        pval = model.pvalues[column_name] # Utiliser le nom de la colonne pour accÃ©der Ã  la p-valeur\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # VÃ©rifier si cette variable est la meilleure (p-valeur la plus basse)\n",
    "        if pval < best_pval and pval < 0.05:  # Seulement si elle est significative\n",
    "            best_pval = pval\n",
    "            best_variable = var\n",
    "\n",
    "    return best_variable, best_pval\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def forward_selection_pval(train, idx_p, idx_t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    SÃ©lection en avant basÃ©e sur la probabilitÃ© critique (p-valeur).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - train : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es d'entraÃ®nement.\n",
    "    - idx_p : Liste des indices des variables prÃ©dictives.\n",
    "    - idx_t : Index de la variable cible dans le DataFrame.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - selected_vars : Liste des indices des variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    selected_vars = []  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "    non_selected_vars = idx_p.copy()  # Variables disponibles pour la sÃ©lection\n",
    "    stop = False  # CritÃ¨re d'arrÃªt\n",
    "\n",
    "    while non_selected_vars and not stop:\n",
    "        # Effectuer une Ã©tape de sÃ©lection\n",
    "        best_var, best_pval = step_selection_pval(train, selected_vars, non_selected_vars, idx_t)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if best_var is not None:  # Si une variable significative a Ã©tÃ© trouvÃ©e\n",
    "            selected_vars.append(best_var)\n",
    "            non_selected_vars.remove(best_var)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            stop = True  # ArrÃªter si aucune variable significative n'est trouvÃ©e\n",
    "\n",
    "        # VÃ©rifier si toutes les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es sont significatives\n",
    "        if selected_vars:\n",
    "            X = train.iloc[:, selected_vars]\n",
    "            y = train.iloc[:, idx_t]\n",
    "            X = sm.add_constant(X)\n",
    "            model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Si une variable sÃ©lectionnÃ©e n'est plus significative, arrÃªter\n",
    "            if not all(model.pvalues[1:] < 0.05):  # Ignorer la constante (indice 0)\n",
    "                stop = True\n",
    "\n",
    "    return selected_vars"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7549ad30",
   "metadata": {},

    "Est-il meilleur que celui utilisant toutes les variables ?"
   ]

    "# Indices des variables prÃ©dictives\n",

      "Meilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ© :\n",
      "Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : ['sqft_living', 'lat', 'waterfront', 'grade', 'yr_built', 'view', 'bedrooms', 'bathrooms', 'zipcode', 'long', 'sqft_above', 'condition', 'sqft_lot15', 'yr_renovated']\n",
      "Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : 4.2360\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def forward_selection_cv(data, predictors, target, cv=10):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    ImplÃ©mente la mÃ©thode de Forward Selection en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE)\n",
    "    basÃ©e sur la validation croisÃ©e comme critÃ¨re de performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - data : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es.\n",
    "    - predictors : Liste des noms des variables prÃ©dictives.\n",
    "    - target : Nom de la variable cible.\n",
    "    - cv : Nombre de folds pour la validation croisÃ©e.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - best_predictors : Liste des variables prÃ©dictives du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    - best_mse : Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    selected_predictors = []  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "    remaining_predictors = predictors.copy()  # Variables restantes Ã  tester\n",
    "    best_mse_fcv = float('inf')  # Initialisez avec une erreur trÃ¨s Ã©levÃ©e\n",
    "    best_predictors = []  # Meilleur ensemble de variables\n",
    "\n",
    "    while remaining_predictors:\n",
    "        iteration_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Testez l'ajout de chaque variable restante\n",
    "        for predictor in remaining_predictors:\n",
    "            # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es + la nouvelle variable\n",
    "            current_predictors = selected_predictors + [predictor]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la validation croisÃ©e\n",
    "            X = data[current_predictors]\n",
    "            y = data[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ModÃ¨le de rÃ©gression linÃ©aire\n",
    "            model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Validation croisÃ©e pour calculer le MSE\n",
    "            mse_scores = -cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=cv, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')\n",
    "            mean_mse_fcv = mse_scores.mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Stocker les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "            iteration_results.append((predictor, mean_mse_fcv))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Trouver la variable qui amÃ©liore le plus la performance\n",
    "        iteration_results = sorted(iteration_results, key=lambda x: x[1])  # Trier par MSE croissant\n",
    "        best_candidate, best_candidate_mse = iteration_results[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Mettre Ã  jour le meilleur modÃ¨le si nÃ©cessaire\n",
    "        if best_candidate_mse < best_mse_fcv:\n",
    "            best_mse_fcv = best_candidate_mse\n",
    "            best_predictors = selected_predictors + [best_candidate]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Ajouter la meilleure variable au modÃ¨le\n",
    "        selected_predictors.append(best_candidate)\n",
    "        remaining_predictors.remove(best_candidate)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Afficher les informations de l'itÃ©ration\n",
    "        print(f\"Variable ajoutÃ©e : {best_candidate}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {best_candidate_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {selected_predictors}\")\n",
    "        print(\"-\" * 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return best_predictors, best_mse_fcv\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Appliquer la mÃ©thode de Forward Selection\n",
    "target = 'price'  # Nom de la variable cible\n",
    "predictors = [col for col in houses.columns if col != target]  # Liste des variables prÃ©dictives\n",
    "\n",
    "best_predictors, best_mse_fcv = forward_selection_cv(houses, predictors, target, cv=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "print(\"\\nMeilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ© :\")\n",
    "print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {best_predictors}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {best_mse_fcv:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },

    "Nous mettons en oeuvre ici, **le backward selection** en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation(train/test split) comme critÃ¨re de performance pour la sÃ©lection des variables et comme critÃ¨re d'arrÃªt, ne vous arrÃªtez pas allez jusqu'au bout et gardez le meilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ©."

      "==============================================================================\n",
      "Omnibus:                     7676.440   Durbin-Watson:                   2.020\n",

   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "def backward_selection(train, test, idx_p, idx_t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    ImplÃ©mente la mÃ©thode de backward selection en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - train : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es d'entraÃ®nement.\n",
    "    - test : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es de test.\n",
    "    - idx_p : Liste des indices des variables prÃ©dictives.\n",
    "    - idx_t : Index de la variable cible.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - best_model : Le meilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ©.\n",
    "    - best_vars : Liste des indices des variables prÃ©dictives du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    - best_mse : Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    current_vars = idx_p.copy()  # Commencez avec toutes les variables prÃ©dictives\n",
    "    best_model = None\n",
    "    best_mse = float('inf')  # Initialisez avec une erreur trÃ¨s Ã©levÃ©e\n",
    "    best_vars = current_vars.copy()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    while current_vars:\n",
    "        # Initialiser les rÃ©sultats pour cette itÃ©ration\n",
    "        iteration_results = []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for var in current_vars:\n",
    "            # CrÃ©ez un sous-ensemble des variables prÃ©dictives sans la variable actuelle\n",
    "            vars_subset = [v for v in current_vars if v != var]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la rÃ©gression\n",
    "            X_train = train.iloc[:, vars_subset]\n",
    "            X_train = sm.add_constant(X_train)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "            y_train = train.iloc[:, idx_t]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            X_test = test.iloc[:, vars_subset]\n",
    "            X_test = sm.add_constant(X_test)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "            y_test = test.iloc[:, idx_t]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "            model = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train).fit()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de test\n",
    "            predictions = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "            mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Stocker les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "            iteration_results.append((var, mse, model, vars_subset))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Trouver la variable Ã  supprimer (celle qui augmente le moins l'erreur)\n",
    "        iteration_results = sorted(iteration_results, key=lambda x: x[1])  # Trier par MSE croissant\n",
    "        worst_var, worst_mse, worst_model, worst_vars_subset = iteration_results[0]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Mettre Ã  jour le meilleur modÃ¨le si nÃ©cessaire\n",
    "        if worst_mse < best_mse:\n",
    "            best_mse = worst_mse\n",
    "            best_model = worst_model\n",
    "            best_vars = worst_vars_subset\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Supprimer la variable avec le plus faible impact\n",
    "        current_vars.remove(worst_var)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # print(f\"Variable supprimÃ©e : {train.columns[worst_var]}\")\n",
    "        # print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {worst_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "        # print(f\"Variables restantes : {[train.columns[v] for v in current_vars]}\")\n",
    "        # print(\"-\" * 50)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return best_model, best_vars, best_mse\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# DÃ©finir les indices des variables prÃ©dictives et de la cible\n",
    "target = 'price'\n",
    "idx_t = houses.columns.get_loc(target)\n",
    "idx_p = [i for i in range(houses.shape[1]) if i != idx_t]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diviser les donnÃ©es en ensembles d'entraÃ®nement et de test\n",
    "train, test = train_test_split(houses, test_size=0.25, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Appliquer la mÃ©thode de backward selection\n",
    "best_model, best_vars, best_mse = backward_selection(train, test, idx_p, idx_t)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "print(\"\\nMeilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ© :\")\n",
    "print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {[houses.columns[v] for v in best_vars]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {best_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(best_model.summary())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

      "Fichier de soumission crÃ©Ã© : submission_backward_selection.csv\n"
     ]

   "source": [
    "# Charger le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition = pd.read_csv('houses_competition.csv', index_col=0)\n",
    "# Supprimer la colonne 'Unnamed: 0' si elle existe\n",
    "competition = competition.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 1 : PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour le modÃ¨le backward_selection\n",
    "# Utiliser les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par backward_selection\n",
    "selected_columns = [houses.columns[v] for v in best_vars]  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par backward_selection\n",
    "X_competition_backward = competition[selected_columns]  # SÃ©lectionner uniquement les colonnes nÃ©cessaires\n",
    "X_competition_backward = sm.add_constant(X_competition_backward)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 2 : PrÃ©dire les prix avec le modÃ¨le backward_selection\n",
    "predictions_backward = best_model.predict(X_competition_backward)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 3 : CrÃ©er le fichier CSV pour soumission\n",
    "submission_backward = pd.DataFrame({'ID': competition.index, 'Price': predictions_backward})\n",
    "submission_backward.to_csv('submission_backward_selection.csv', index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fichier de soumission crÃ©Ã© : submission_backward_selection.csv\")"
   ]

    "mse_all = mean_squared_error(y_test_all, predictions_all)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) pour toutes les variables : {mse_all:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# MSE pour le modÃ¨le avec variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es avec la mÃ©thode backward_selection\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) pour les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {best_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Comparer les deux modÃ¨les\n",
    "if best_mse < mse_all:\n",
    "    print(\"Le modÃ¨le utilisant les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es (backward selection) est meilleur.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Le modÃ¨le utilisant toutes les variables est meilleur.\")"

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3d478335",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Nous mettons en oeuvre , le backward selection en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation(Cross-validation) comme critÃ¨re de performance pour la sÃ©lection des variables et comme critÃ¨re d'arrÃªt, arrÃªtez-vous lorsqu'aucun meilleur modÃ¨le n'a Ã©tÃ© trouvÃ© depuis Î´ = 5 itÃ©rations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 455,
   "id": "635957b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "def backward_selection_cv(data, predictors, target, delta=5, cv=10):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    ImplÃ©mente la mÃ©thode de backward selection en utilisant l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE)\n",
    "    basÃ©e sur la validation croisÃ©e comme critÃ¨re de performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - data : DataFrame contenant les donnÃ©es.\n",
    "    - predictors : Liste des noms des variables prÃ©dictives.\n",
    "    - target : Nom de la variable cible.\n",
    "    - delta : Nombre maximal d'itÃ©rations sans amÃ©lioration avant d'arrÃªter.\n",
    "    - cv : Nombre de folds pour la validation croisÃ©e.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - best_model : Le meilleur modÃ¨le trouvÃ©.\n",
    "    - best_predictors : Liste des variables prÃ©dictives du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    - best_mse : Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) du meilleur modÃ¨le.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    current_predictors = predictors.copy()  # Commencez avec toutes les variables prÃ©dictives\n",
    "    best_mse_cv = float('inf')  # Initialisez avec une erreur trÃ¨s Ã©levÃ©e\n",
    "    best_predictors = current_predictors.copy()\n",
    "    no_improvement_count = 0  # Compteur pour les itÃ©rations sans amÃ©lioration\n",
    "\n",
    "    while current_predictors and no_improvement_count < delta:\n",
    "        iteration_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Testez la suppression de chaque variable\n",
    "        for predictor in current_predictors:\n",
    "            # Variables restantes aprÃ¨s suppression\n",
    "            predictors_subset = [p for p in current_predictors if p != predictor]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour la validation croisÃ©e\n",
    "            X = data[predictors_subset]\n",
    "            y = data[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ModÃ¨le de rÃ©gression linÃ©aire\n",
    "            model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Validation croisÃ©e pour calculer le MSE\n",
    "            mse_scores = -cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=cv, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')\n",
    "            mean_mse_cv = mse_scores.mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Stocker les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "            iteration_results.append((predictor, mean_mse_cv, predictors_subset))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Trouver la variable dont la suppression donne le meilleur MSE\n",
    "        iteration_results = sorted(iteration_results, key=lambda x: x[1])  # Trier par MSE croissant\n",
    "        worst_predictor, worst_mse_cv, worst_predictors_subset = iteration_results[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # VÃ©rifiez si le nouveau modÃ¨le est meilleur\n",
    "        if worst_mse_cv < best_mse_cv:\n",
    "            best_mse_cv = worst_mse_cv\n",
    "            best_predictors = worst_predictors_subset\n",
    "            no_improvement_count = 0  # RÃ©initialiser le compteur\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            no_improvement_count += 1  # IncrÃ©menter le compteur\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Supprimer la variable avec le plus faible impact\n",
    "        current_predictors.remove(worst_predictor)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Afficher les informations de l'itÃ©ration\n",
    "        print(f\"Variable supprimÃ©e : {worst_predictor}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) : {worst_mse_cv:.4f}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"Variables restantes : {current_predictors}\")\n",
    "        print(\"-\" * 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return best_predictors, best_mse_cv"
   ]
  },
  {

    "5. ModÃ¨les non linÃ©aires : ajoutez quelques variables non linÃ©aires (que vous pouvez coupler avec des techniques de sÃ©lection de \n",
    "variables) pour essayer de concevoir des modÃ¨les plus prÃ©cis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4e2012e8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Fonction permet d'ajouter facilement des caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales Ã  un jeu de donnÃ©es.\n",
    "Les paramÃ¨tres de cette fonction sontÂ :\n",
    "- dataÂ : le jeu de donnÃ©es considÃ©rÃ© (train, test ou autre)\n",
    "- idx_pÂ : la liste des index de colonnes de data pour lesquels vous souhaitez ajouter des caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales\n",
    "- powerÂ : la liste des puissances Ã  utiliser pour les variables de idx_p\n",
    "Par exemple, l'appel add_polynomial_feature(train, [1], [2]) ajoutera une nouvelle variable correspondant Ã  x1 (colonne 1 du train) avec une puissance 2 (au carrÃ©)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 306,
   "id": "123c70f6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def add_polynomial_feature(data, idx_p, power):\n",
    "    new_data = data.copy(deep = True)\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(idx_p)):\n",
    "        for j in power:\n",
    "            for k in range(2, j+1):\n",
    "                new_data['{}_pow_{}'.format(new_data.columns[idx_p[i]],k)] = new_data.iloc[:,idx_p[i]]**k\n",
    "    return(new_data)"
   ]
  },
  {

    "X_train_poly = train_poly[['sqft_living', 'sqft_living_pow_2', 'sqft_living_pow_3']]\n",
    "X_train_poly = sm.add_constant(X_train_poly)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "y_train = train['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "model_poly = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train_poly).fit()\n",

   "source": [
    "Ã‰tape 3 : Ã‰valuer l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation\n",
    "Nous utilisons l'ensemble de test pour Ã©valuer la performance du modÃ¨le avec les nouvelles caractÃ©ristiques.\n",
    "\n",
    "Exemple : Calcul de l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 309,
   "id": "53e5a7cf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) avec les caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales : 6.5943\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es de test\n",
    "X_test_poly = test_poly[['sqft_living', 'sqft_living_pow_2', 'sqft_living_pow_3']]\n",
    "X_test_poly = sm.add_constant(X_test_poly)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "y_test = test['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dictions sur l'ensemble de test\n",
    "predictions_poly = model_poly.predict(X_test_poly)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "mse_poly = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions_poly)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) avec les caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales : {mse_poly:.4f}\")"

    "\n",
    "# Ajuster le modÃ¨le\n",
    "model_selected_poly = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train_selected).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 2 : PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es de test\n",

     ]

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Charger le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition = pd.read_csv('houses_competition.csv', index_col=0)\n",
    "# Supprimer la colonne 'Unnamed: 0' si elle existe\n",
    "competition = competition.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 1 : Ajouter les caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales nÃ©cessaires\n",
    "competition_poly = add_polynomial_feature(competition, \n",
    "                                          [competition.columns.get_loc('sqft_living'), competition.columns.get_loc('bedrooms')], \n",
    "                                          [2, 2])  # Ajouter les puissances pour sqft_living et bedrooms\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 2 : PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour le modÃ¨le polynomial\n",
    "X_competition_poly = competition_poly[best_predictors_sfcv]  # Utiliser uniquement les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_competition_poly = sm.add_constant(X_competition_poly)  # Ajouter une constante\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 3 : PrÃ©dire les prix avec le modÃ¨le polynomial\n",
    "predictions_poly = model_selected_poly_sfcv.predict(X_competition_poly)\n",

    "print(houses_poly.head())"

    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diviser les donnÃ©es en train et test\n",
    "train, test = train_test_split(houses, test_size=0.25, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ModÃ¨le avec toutes les variables prÃ©dictives\n",
    "X_train = train[predictors]\n",
    "y_train = train['price']\n",
    "X_test = test[predictors]\n",
    "y_test = test['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# EntraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le\n",
    "model_all = LinearRegression()\n",
    "model_all.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dictions et calcul de l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation\n",
    "predictions_all = model_all.predict(X_test)\n",
    "mse_all_polynome = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions_all)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) pour toutes les variables : {mse_all_polynome:.4f}\")"
   ]

    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 2 : Appliquer la mÃ©thode backward_selection pour sÃ©lectionner les meilleures variables\n",
    "# DÃ©finir les indices des variables prÃ©dictives et de la cible\n",
    "idx_t = train_poly.columns.get_loc('price')  # Index de la variable cible\n",
    "idx_p = [i for i in range(train_poly.shape[1]) if i != idx_t]  # Indices des variables prÃ©dictives\n",
    "\n",
    "# Appliquer la mÃ©thode backward_selection\n",
    "best_model, best_vars, best_mse = backward_selection(train_poly, test_poly, idx_p, idx_t)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 3 : CrÃ©er un modÃ¨le avec les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "selected_columns = [train_poly.columns[v] for v in best_vars]  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "X_train_selected = train_poly[selected_columns]\n",
    "y_train_selected = train_poly['price']\n",
    "X_test_selected = test_poly[selected_columns]\n",
    "y_test_selected = test_poly['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# EntraÃ®ner le modÃ¨le\n",
    "model_selected = LinearRegression()\n",
    "model_selected.fit(X_train_selected, y_train_selected)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 4 : PrÃ©dictions et calcul de l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation\n",
    "predictions_selected = model_selected.predict(X_test_selected)\n",
    "mse_selected_polynome = mean_squared_error(y_test_selected, predictions_selected)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE) pour les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {mse_selected_polynome:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es : {selected_columns}\")"
   ]

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "# Charger le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition = pd.read_csv('houses_competition.csv', index_col=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Supprimer la colonne 'Unnamed: 0' si elle existe\n",
    "competition = competition.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ajouter les caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales nÃ©cessaires pour le dataset de compÃ©tition\n",
    "competition_poly = add_polynomial_feature(\n",
    "    competition,\n",
    "    [competition.columns.get_loc(col) for col in predictors],  # Ajouter les puissances pour toutes les variables prÃ©dictives\n",
    "    [2]  # Ajouter des caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales de degrÃ© 2\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©parer les donnÃ©es pour le modÃ¨le avec les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "selected_columns = [train_poly.columns[v] for v in best_vars]  # Variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es par backward_selection\n",
    "X_competition_selected = competition_poly[selected_columns]  # Utiliser uniquement les colonnes nÃ©cessaires\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire les prix avec le modÃ¨le basÃ© sur les variables sÃ©lectionnÃ©es\n",
    "predictions_competition = model_selected.predict(X_competition_selected)\n",
    "\n",

    "print(f\"Colonnes manquantes : {missing_columns}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ajouter les colonnes manquantes avec des valeurs par dÃ©faut (0)\n",
    "for col in missing_columns:\n",
    "    competition_poly[col] = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "# RÃ©ordonner les colonnes pour correspondre Ã  l'ordre attendu par le modÃ¨le\n",
    "X_competition_final = competition_poly[selected_columns_bwd]\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire les prix avec le modÃ¨le final\n",
    "predictions_competition = final_model.predict(X_competition_final)\n",
    "\n",
    "# CrÃ©er le fichier CSV pour soumission\n",
    "submission_final = pd.DataFrame({'ID': competition.index, 'Price': predictions_competition})\n",
    "submission_final.to_csv('submission_model_forward_selection_cv_backward_selection.csv', index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fichier de soumission crÃ©Ã© : submission_model_forward_selection_cv_backward_selection.csv\")"
   ]
  },

    "Analyse exploratoire\n",
    "Nous analysons la sÃ©rie temporelle pour identifier les tendances, la saisonnalitÃ© et les Ã©ventuelles anomalies. Cela peut inclure :\n",
    "\n",
    "La dÃ©composition de la sÃ©rie temporelle en composantes (tendance, saisonnalitÃ©, rÃ©sidus).\n",
    "La visualisation des statistiques descriptives."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 665,
   "id": "35e09329",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose\n",
    "\n",
    "# Decompose the time series\n",
    "decomposition = seasonal_decompose(alcohol_data, model='additive', period=12)  # Try 'additive' as well\n",
    "decomposition.plot()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Inspect the components\n",
    "trend = decomposition.trend\n",
    "seasonal = decomposition.seasonal\n",
    "residual = decomposition.resid\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# La dÃ©composition permet d'observer les Ã©lÃ©ments suivantsÂ :\n",
    "# 1. TendanceÂ : Si la composante de tendance prÃ©sente un mouvement clair Ã  la hausse ou Ã  la baisse au fil du temps, cela indique la prÃ©sence d'une tendance dans les donnÃ©es.\n",
    "# 2. Composante saisonniÃ¨reÂ : Si l'amplitude de la composante saisonniÃ¨re varie proportionnellement au niveau des donnÃ©es, cela suggÃ¨re un modÃ¨le multiplicatif.\n",
    "# Dans le cas contraire, si l'amplitude reste constante, cela suggÃ¨re un modÃ¨le additif.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the autocorrelation function (ACF)\n",
    "plot_acf(alcohol_data.dropna(), lags=50, title=\"Autocorrelation Function (ACF)\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "# Based on the decomposition, we can conclude:\n",
    "# - If the trend component shows a clear upward or downward movement over time, there is a trend in the data.\n",
    "# - If the seasonal component exhibits repeating patterns at regular intervals, there is a seasonal component.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check for trend and seasonality\n",
    "if trend.isnull().all():\n",
    "    print(\"No clear trend detected.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"A trend component is present.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if seasonal.abs().sum() > 0:\n",
    "    print(\"A seasonal component is present.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No clear seasonal component detected.\")"
   ]

    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer les prÃ©dictions pour l'ensemble de validation\n",
    "predictions_validation = model_additive.forecast(len(test_data))\n",
    "\n",
    "# ReprÃ©senter graphiquement les donnÃ©es d'apprentissage, de validation et les prÃ©dictions\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(train_data, label=\"Ensemble d'entraÃ®nement\", color=\"blue\")\n",
    "plt.plot(test_data, label=\"Ensemble de validation\", color=\"orange\")\n",
    "plt.plot(test_data.index, predictions_validation, label=\"PrÃ©dictions TES\", color=\"green\", linestyle=\"--\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"PrÃ©dictions TES sur l'ensemble de validation\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Date\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Consommation\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) sur l'ensemble de validation\n",
    "mse_validation_tes_additive = mean_squared_error(test_data, predictions_validation)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) sur l'ensemble de validation : {mse_validation_tes_additive:.4f}\")"

   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.tsa.ar_model import AutoReg\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tester diffÃ©rents ordres pour le modÃ¨le AR\n",
    "max_lag = 20  # Nombre maximum de retards (p) Ã  tester\n",
    "mse_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for lag in range(1, max_lag + 1):\n",
    "    # Ajuster le modÃ¨le AR\n",
    "    model_ar = AutoReg(train_data, lags=lag).fit()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de validation\n",
    "    predictions = model_ar.predict(start=len(train_data), end=len(train_data) + len(test_data) - 1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "    mse = mean_squared_error(test_data, predictions)\n",
    "    mse_results.append((lag, mse))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Ordre AR(p): {lag}, MSE: {mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Trouver le meilleur ordre AR\n",
    "best_lag, best_mse = min(mse_results, key=lambda x: x[1])\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMeilleur ordre AR(p): {best_lag}, avec MSE: {best_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ajuster le modÃ¨le final avec le meilleur ordre\n",
    "model_final = AutoReg(train_data, lags=best_lag).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de validation\n",
    "predictions_final = model_final.predict(start=len(train_data), end=len(train_data) + len(test_data) - 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ReprÃ©senter graphiquement les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(train_data, label=\"Ensemble d'entraÃ®nement\", color=\"blue\")\n",
    "plt.plot(test_data, label=\"Ensemble de validation\", color=\"orange\")\n",
    "plt.plot(test_data.index, predictions_final, label=f\"PrÃ©dictions AR({best_lag})\", color=\"green\", linestyle=\"--\")\n",
    "plt.title(f\"PrÃ©dictions AR({best_lag}) sur l'ensemble de validation\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Date\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Consommation\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) pour le modÃ¨le final\n",
    "final_mse_no_trend_no_saison = mean_squared_error(test_data, predictions_final)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) pour le modÃ¨le final AR({best_lag}): {final_mse_no_trend_no_saison:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },

      "Erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) pour le modÃ¨le final AR(17) avec tendance : 184212.2611\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.tsa.ar_model import AutoReg\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "# Charger les donnÃ©es Alcohol.csv\n",
    "alcohol_data = pd.read_csv('Alcohol.csv', sep=';', parse_dates=['Date'], dayfirst=True)\n",
    "alcohol_data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diviser les donnÃ©es en ensembles d'entraÃ®nement (80%) et de validation (20%)\n",
    "train_size = int(len(alcohol_data) * 0.8)\n",
    "train_data = alcohol_data.iloc[:train_size]\n",
    "validation_data = alcohol_data.iloc[train_size:]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tester diffÃ©rents ordres pour le modÃ¨le AR avec tendance\n",
    "max_lag = 20  # Nombre maximum de retards (p) Ã  tester\n",
    "mse_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for lag in range(1, max_lag + 1):\n",
    "    # Ajuster le modÃ¨le AR avec tendance\n",
    "    ar_trend_model = AutoReg(train_data['Volume'], lags=lag, trend='t').fit()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de validation\n",
    "    ar_trend_predictions = ar_trend_model.predict(start=validation_data.index[0], end=validation_data.index[-1])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE)\n",
    "    mse = mean_squared_error(validation_data['Volume'], ar_trend_predictions)\n",
    "    mse_results.append((lag, mse))\n",
    "    print(f\"Ordre AR(p): {lag}, MSE: {mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Trouver le meilleur ordre AR\n",
    "best_order, best_mse = min(mse_results, key=lambda x: x[1])\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMeilleur ordre AR(p): {best_order}, avec MSE: {best_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ajuster le modÃ¨le final avec le meilleur ordre\n",
    "ar_trend_model_final = AutoReg(train_data['Volume'], lags=best_order, trend='t').fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# PrÃ©dire sur l'ensemble de validation\n",
    "ar_trend_predictions_final = ar_trend_model_final.predict(start=validation_data.index[0], end=validation_data.index[-1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tracer les ensembles d'entraÃ®nement, de validation et les prÃ©dictions\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(train_data.index, train_data['Volume'], label='Ensemble d\\'entraÃ®nement', color='blue')\n",
    "plt.plot(validation_data.index, validation_data['Volume'], label='Ensemble de validation', color='orange')\n",
    "plt.plot(validation_data.index, ar_trend_predictions_final, label=f'PrÃ©dictions AR({best_order}) avec tendance', color='green', linestyle='--')\n",
    "plt.title('SÃ©rie temporelle Alcohol : EntraÃ®nement, Validation et PrÃ©dictions AR avec tendance')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Consommation d\\'alcool')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer l'erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) pour le modÃ¨le final\n",
    "final_mse_with_trend = mean_squared_error(validation_data['Volume'], ar_trend_predictions_final)\n",
    "print(f\"Erreur quadratique moyenne (MSE) pour le modÃ¨le final AR({best_order}) avec tendance : {final_mse_with_trend:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.tsa.ar_model import AutoReg\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize a list to store AIC values for different orders\n",
    "ars_aic_values = []\n",
    "orders = range(1, 21)  # Test ARS models with orders from 1 to 20\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loop through different orders and fit the ARS model\n",
    "for order in orders:\n",
    "    ars_model = AutoReg(train_data['Volume'], lags=order, seasonal=True, period=12).fit()\n",
    "    ars_aic_values.append((order, ars_model.aic))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find the order with the lowest AIC\n",
    "best_ars_order = min(ars_aic_values, key=lambda x: x[1])\n",
    "print(f\"Best ARS order: {best_ars_order[0]} with AIC: {best_ars_order[1]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot AIC values for different orders\n",
    "ars_orders, ars_aic_scores = zip(*ars_aic_values)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(ars_orders, ars_aic_scores, marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('AIC Values for Different ARS Model Orders')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Order')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('AIC')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.tsa.ar_model import AutoReg\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize a list to store MSE values for different orders\n",
    "ars_trend_mse_values = []\n",
    "orders = range(1, 21)  # Test ARS models with orders from 1 to 20\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loop through different orders and fit the ARS model with trend\n",
    "for order in orders:\n",
    "    ars_trend_model = AutoReg(train_data['Volume'], lags=order, trend='t', seasonal=True, period=12).fit()\n",
    "    ars_trend_predictions = ars_trend_model.predict(start=validation_data.index[0], end=validation_data.index[-1])\n",
    "    mse = mean_squared_error(validation_data['Volume'], ars_trend_predictions)\n",
    "    ars_trend_mse_values.append((order, mse))\n",
    "    print(f\"Order ARS(p): {order}, MSE: {mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find the order with the lowest MSE\n",
    "best_ars_trend_order, best_ars_trend_mse = min(ars_trend_mse_values, key=lambda x: x[1])\n",
    "print(f\"\\nBest ARS order with trend: {best_ars_trend_order}, with MSE: {best_ars_trend_mse:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit the final ARS model with trend using the best order\n",
    "ars_trend_model_final = AutoReg(train_data['Volume'], lags=best_ars_trend_order, trend='t', seasonal=True, period=12).fit()\n",
    "ars_trend_predictions_final = ars_trend_model_final.predict(start=validation_data.index[0], end=validation_data.index[-1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the training, validation data, and predictions\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(train_data.index, train_data['Volume'], label='Training Set', color='blue')\n",
    "plt.plot(validation_data.index, validation_data['Volume'], label='Validation Set', color='orange')\n",
    "plt.plot(validation_data.index, ars_trend_predictions_final, label=f'ARS({best_ars_trend_order}) with Trend Predictions', color='green', linestyle='--')\n",
    "plt.title('Volume Time Series: Training, Validation, and ARS with Trend Predictions')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Volume')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute the squared prediction error on the validation set\n",
    "ars_trend_squared_error = mean_squared_error(validation_data['Volume'], ars_trend_predictions_final)\n",
    "print(f\"Squared Prediction Error on Validation Set (ARS with Trend): {ars_trend_squared_error:.4f}\")"
   ]

    "from statsmodels.tsa.ar_model import AutoReg\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# On suppose que ta sÃ©rie s'appelle 'alcohol' (Series pandas avec un index temporel mensuel)\n",
    "# Et que best_ars_trend_order est dÃ©fini d'aprÃ¨s ton code prÃ©cÃ©dent\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 1 : Ajuster le modÃ¨le ARS avec tendance sur toute la sÃ©rie\n",
    "final_ars_trend_model = AutoReg(alcohol_data, lags=best_ars_trend_order, trend='t', seasonal=True, period=12).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 2 : PrÃ©dire les 24 prochains mois\n",
    "future_predictions = final_ars_trend_model.predict(start=len(alcohol_data), end=len(alcohol_data) + 23)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 3 : GÃ©nÃ©rer les dates futures\n",
    "future_index = pd.date_range(start=alcohol_data.index[-1] + pd.DateOffset(months=1), periods=24, freq='M')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 4 : Tracer la sÃ©rie complÃ¨te + les prÃ©dictions\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(alcohol_data.index, alcohol_data, label='SÃ©rie rÃ©elle Alcohol', color='blue')\n",
    "plt.plot(future_index, future_predictions, label='PrÃ©dictions futures (ARS avec tendance)', color='red', linestyle='--')\n",
    "plt.title('PrÃ©dictions Alcohol - ARS avec tendance (2024-2025)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Volume d\\'alcool')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 5 : Afficher les prÃ©dictions\n",
    "print(\"ðŸ“…PrÃ©dictions pour Janvier 2024 Ã  DÃ©cembre 2025 :\")\n",
    "print(future_predictions)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ã‰tape 5 : Sauvegarde dans un fichier texte\n",
    "output_file = 'Predictions_ARS_2024_2025_Loic_&_Cyril.txt'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ouvrir le fichier et Ã©crire les rÃ©sultats\n",
    "with open(output_file, 'w') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(\"Date\\tVolume\\n\")  # En-tÃªtes\n",
    "    for date, value in zip(future_index, future_predictions):\n",
    "        f.write(f\"{date.strftime('%Y-%m')}\\t{value:.2f}\\n\")  # Date + valeur prÃ©dite avec 2 dÃ©cimales\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"âœ… Les prÃ©dictions ont Ã©tÃ© enregistrÃ©es dans : {output_file}\")\n"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4f249a7e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "AprÃ¨s avoir explorÃ© et comparÃ© diffÃ©rents modÃ¨les de rÃ©gression linÃ©aire et non linÃ©aire, voici les points clÃ©s :\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **ModÃ¨les linÃ©aires simples** :\n",
    "    - Les modÃ¨les utilisant une seule variable prÃ©dictive (comme `sqft_living`) sont simples Ã  interprÃ©ter mais ont une performance limitÃ©e en termes de prÃ©cision.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **ModÃ¨les linÃ©aires multiples** :\n",
    "    - L'utilisation de toutes les variables prÃ©dictives amÃ©liore la performance par rapport aux modÃ¨les simples, mais peut introduire des problÃ¨mes de sur-ajustement si certaines variables ne sont pas pertinentes.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **SÃ©lection de variables** :\n",
    "    - Les techniques comme **Forward Selection** et **Backward Selection** permettent de rÃ©duire le nombre de variables tout en maintenant ou amÃ©liorant la performance. Ces mÃ©thodes sont particuliÃ¨rement utiles pour Ã©viter la surabondance de variables inutiles.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **CaractÃ©ristiques polynomiales** :\n",
    "    - L'ajout de caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales (comme `sqft_living^2` ou `sqft_living^3`) amÃ©liore la capacitÃ© du modÃ¨le Ã  capturer des relations non linÃ©aires dans les donnÃ©es. Cependant, cela peut Ã©galement augmenter la complexitÃ© et le risque de sur-ajustement.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. **Validation croisÃ©e** :\n",
    "    - L'utilisation de la validation croisÃ©e pour Ã©valuer les modÃ¨les garantit une estimation plus robuste de l'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation, en particulier pour les modÃ¨les complexes.\n",
    "\n",
    "6. **Meilleur modÃ¨le** :\n",
    "    - Le modÃ¨le combinant **Forward Selection** avec des caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales et une validation croisÃ©e a montrÃ© la meilleure performance en termes d'erreur de gÃ©nÃ©ralisation (MSE). Cela indique que l'ajout de non-linÃ©aritÃ©s et la sÃ©lection rigoureuse des variables sont bÃ©nÃ©fiques.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Recommandation\n",
    "- Pour des prÃ©dictions prÃ©cises, il est recommandÃ© d'utiliser un modÃ¨le combinant des caractÃ©ristiques polynomiales et une sÃ©lection de variables avec validation croisÃ©e.\n",
    "- Cependant, la complexitÃ© du modÃ¨le doit Ãªtre Ã©quilibrÃ©e avec l'interprÃ©tabilitÃ©, en fonction des besoins du projet."
   ]
  }
 ],
